Plot a Grouped Transition Network Analysis Model

Source: R/plot.R
plot.group_tna.Rd

Plots a transition network of each cluster using qgraph.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'group_tna'
plot(x, title, ...)

Arguments

x

A group_model object.

title

A title for each plot. It can be a single string (the same one will be used for all plots) or a list (one per group)

...

Same as plot.tna().

Value

NULL (invisibly).

See also

Basic functions build_model(), hist.group_tna(), hist.tna(), plot.tna(), plot_mosaic(), plot_mosaic.group_tna(), plot_mosaic.tna_data(), prepare_data(), print.group_tna(), print.summary.group_tna(), print.summary.tna(), print.tna(), print.tna_data(), summary.group_tna(), summary.tna(), tna-package

Examples

model <- group_model(engagement_mmm)
plot(model)
